==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: kumquat
<hw>kum"quat</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Chin. <ets>kin
keu</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>any of several trees or shrubs
of the genus <gen>Fortunella</gen> (formerly <gen>Citrus</gen>) of the
rue family (<fam>Rutaceae</fam>) (especially <spn>Citrus Japonica</spn>)
growing in <country>China</country> and <country>Japan</country> bearing
small orange-colored edible fruits with thick sweet-flavored skin and
sour pulp; also, any of the small acid, orange-colored citrus fruits of
such plants, used mostly for preserves.</def> <altsp>[Also spelled
<asp>cumquat</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Kupfernickel</ent>⟦br⟧
